DAMATURU – The National Directorate of Employment (NDE), Yobe State Office has engaged 50 youths on entrepreneurship skills under the Enterprises and Counselling Clinic (NDE-efcc) programme. The five days training was supervised by the Small Scale department of the commission. Speaking at the graduation ceremony of the training, the NDE Director-General, Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo urged the participants to take the advantage of the programme and improve their skills for a successful business. Represented by the NDE State Coordinator, Mr John T Kwaji, Fikpo noted that the essence of the training was to expose the participants to requisite entrepreneurship skills. He said that during the training he has also taken the participants on procedures of securing and managing loans from various financial institutions. In his address, the NDE Head of Department, Small Scale Enterprises (SSE) Yobe State directorate,  Abba Adamu explained that the beneficiaries had undergone five days long training in order to be familiar with all the necessary skills. He called on the participants to apply skills and knowledge they learned to grow their businesses. Ali Mohammed who spoke on behalf of the participants has commended the Federal government for the gesture adding that with the training they would take their businesses to next level.